edu.umass.cs.protocoltask.json

Class ProtocolPacket<NodeIDType,EventType>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.protocoltask.json.ProtocolPacket<NodeIDType,EventType>
  • Type Parameters:
    NodeIDType -
    EventType - This class is concretized to use integer node IDs, long keys, and JSON messages, but the PacketType is left generic. The reason is so that implementors can define and use their own packet types. Note that it is not possible to extend the enum Packet.PacketType and it is not modular to have to put *all* packet types in the Packet class.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProtocolEvent<EventType,java.lang.String>, ThresholdProtocolEvent<NodeIDType,EventType,java.lang.String>, Keyable<java.lang.String>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PingPongPacket, ReconfigurationPacket
